        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 3:30PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 330 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lake Summerset, or 11 miles south of Brodhead, moving north at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could cause minor tree limb damage and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Davis, Rock City, Rock Grove, Afolkey, and Lake Summerset.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring and may lead to localized flooding.
Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways. Stay away from
flooded areas. Report any flooding to local law enforcement.</instruction>
